to Michael since practice yesterday?"

286
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:06,025
I said, "I haven't had a chance. We will."
Then Michael came out.

287
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,193
I reached over, grabbed him,
kissed him on the cheek.

288
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:09,862
I said, "I love him. He loves me."

289
00:17:09,945 --> 00:17:12,698
- Would you come here so we can kiss on TV?
- Here we go.

290
00:17:13,198 --> 00:17:16,535
- Would you tell them everything is fine?
- Aww.

291
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:18,680
We've kissed and made up now.

292
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:24,543
I coached him for three years,
from the '86-'87 season through '88-'89.

293
00:17:25,794 --> 00:17:29,089
When I was coaching him,
he was the MVP of the league.

294
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:31,133
<i>...in deep, scoops it in!</i>

295
00:17:31,842 --> 00:17:34,011
He was the MVP
of the All-Star Game.

296
00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:39,600
He won the slam dunk competition...

297
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:42,978
and he was
the Defensive Player of the Year.

298
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:44,622
<i>...pass stolen by Jordan.</i>

299
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:47,941
<i>Michael Jordan takes it
coast-to-coast. Whoo!</i>

300
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:50,110
That's greatness.

301
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:52,821
You know, I mean,
he was now the best player.

